<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 2:42PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Ottawa, Erie and
northeastern Sandusky Counties through 330 PM EDT...
At 241 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Port Clinton, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Sandusky, Western Vermilion, Port Clinton, Kelleys Island,
Put-In-Bay, Oak Harbor, Castalia, Catawba Island, Marblehead, Berlin
Heights, Rocky Ridge, Sandusky South, Birmingham, Fairview Lanes and
Whites Landing.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
